## Backend Infrastructure Improvements

### Centralized Error Handling
Moved away from repetitive `try-catch` blocks to a cleaner, more robust system.
- **[asyncHandler.js](file:///d:/project/Funiture/Backend/utils/asyncHandler.js)**: A utility to wrap async routes and catch errors automatically.
- **[CustomError.js](file:///d:/project/Funiture/Backend/utils/CustomError.js)**: A dedicated error class for managing HTTP status codes.
- **[errorMiddleware.js](file:///d:/project/Funiture/Backend/middleware/errorMiddleware.js)**: A global middleware that catches all errors and provides consistent JSON responses.

### Scalable Caching Strategy
Improved the Redis implementation for better multi-user support.
- **User-Specific Keys**: Cached data now uses `user:${id}` keys instead of a single "User" key, preventing data collisions between different users.
- **Auth Fallback**: The **Auth middleware** now checks the cache first and falls back to the database if needed, ensuring high performance even if the cache is cleared.
- **Simplified Helper**: Refactored [redisHelper.js](file:///d:/project/Funiture/Backend/utils/redisHelper.js) to handle data serialization automatically.

---

## How to Verify
1.  **Frontend**: Navigate to `/about` and `/contact` to see the new designs.
2.  **Backend**: Errors will now return a consistent JSON format like:
    ```json
    {
      "status": "fail",
      "message": "User not found"
    }
    ```
3.  **Caching**: When a user logs in, check your Redis instance to see the `user:<id>` key.

> [!TIP]
> You can now easily add more controllers by simply wrapping them in [asyncHandler](file:///d:/project/Funiture/Backend/utils/asyncHandler.js#1-4) and throwing [CustomError](file:///d:/project/Funiture/Backend/utils/CustomError.js#1-11) whenever something goes wrong!
